race.comment: Tough race with several first starters. ALPINE LEE (12) brings some raceday experience and caught the eye when running on at the end of a 1000m metropolitan maiden. The form has stood up with the winner subsequently winning in stronger grade. She maps to settle closer and will be hard to beat. LUDINA (14) is a well-bred filly from an astute stable. She is drawn well and has shown glimpses of nice ability at the trials. Expect she can measure up on debut. GLASS BAY (5) can run a cheeky race first-up for the new stable, while JOHNNY THE JET (8) is a first starter from a good stable and deserves some thought.
